        "category": "summary",
        "text": "Important: libblockdev security update",
        "title": "Topic"
      },
      {
        "category": "description",
        "text": "The libblockdev packages provide a C library with GObject introspection support used for low-level operations on block devices. The library serves as a thin wrapper around plug-ins for specific functionality, such as LVM, Btrfs, LUKS, or MD RAID.\n\nSecurity Fix(es):\n\n* libblockdev: LPE from allow_active to root in libblockdev via udisks (CVE-2025-6019)\n\nFor more details about the security issue(s), including the impact, a CVSS score, acknowledgments, and other related information, refer to the CVE page(s) listed in the References section.\n\nThis advisory is provided by Ctrl IQ, Inc for Rocky Linux systems. For more information about CIQ security practices, visit https://ciq.com/security.",
        "title": "Description"
      }
